name: Gajanan
bio: At the helm of the Google Developers Group on Campus, I'm at the forefront of fostering innovation and supporting developer communities. My journey through tech leadership was paved at SWAG Developer's Club, where I championed events that bolstered practical tech skills among peers. As a final-year Computer Science student at Shri Guru Gobind Singhji Institute of Engineering and Technology, my academic insights complement my practical endeavors. My Android development proficiency is instrumental in crafting mobile solutions that resonate with users.

name: Sushil
bio: I am Sushil Bhoybar, a final-year Computer Science Engineering student at SGGSIE&T, Nanded, and a Co-organiser at GDG on Campus. I specialize in organizing and managing hackathons, workshops, and technical events. My passion lies in exploring technologies like AI, cloud computing, and cybersecurity. Through my involvement with GDG and other developer communities, I strive to foster innovation, inspire creativity, and create impactful projects.
